quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  7,105,"worthy of saying nothing about Allah except the truth. I have come to you with a clear sign from your Lord. So, let the children of Isra'il go with me.""
  7,106,"He said, 'If you have come with a sign, bring it out, if you are one of the truthful.""
  7,107,"So he threw down his staff, and it was a serpent, manifest;"
  7,108,"and drew out his hand, and it was a white light to the onlookers."
  7,109,"The chiefs of the people of the Pharaoh said, "This man is certainly a sorcerer of great knowledge."
  7,110,"He wants to expel you from your land. So, what do you suggest ?""
  7,111,"They said, 'leave him and his brother alone for a while, and send men to the cities to collect"
  7,112,"and bring to you every expert sorcerer.""
  7,113,"And the sorcerers came to Pharaoh. They said, "There must be a reward for us, if we are the victors.""
  7,114,"He said, "yes, and of course, you will be among the closer ones.""
  7,115,"They said, "0 Musa either you throw (first) or shall we be the ones to throw?" He said, "You throw.""
  7,116,"So when they threw, they bewitched the eyes of the people, and made them frightened, and produced great sorcery."
  7,117,"And We revealed to Musa, 'Throw your staff." Then of a sudden, it began to swallow all that they had concocted."
  7,118,"So, the truth prevailed, and what they were doing became a nullity."
  7,119,"So, they were overcome there and turned humiliated."
  7,120,"And the sorcerers were constrained to fall in prostration."